1. add new file or directory
fistly get update use "git fetch"
(a). use command : git add . #tell git to take a snapshot of the contents of all files under the current directory
(b). creat the files or directories you want
(c). use command : git add files directories #add their updated contents to the index
(d). use command : git commit #prompt you for a message describing the changes
(e). use command : git commit -a -m "***" #add the commitment describeing the changes
(f). use command : git push remote-name branch-name #push to the branch
next step is to update the local repository
(g). use command : git fetch remote-name #get the update of remote-name
(h). use command : git merge remote-name/branch #merge the update with the local repusitory


2. modify a file
fistly get update use "git fetch"
(a). modify the files
(b). use command : git commit #prompt you for a message describing the changes
(c). use command : git commit -a -m "***" #add the commitment describeing the changes
(e). use command : git push remote-name branch-name #push to the branch
next step is to update the local repository
(f). use command : git fetch remote-name #get the update of remote-name
(g). use command : git merge remote-name/branch #merge the update with the local repusitory

3. How to generate a ssh-key and add to ssh
(1) Generate a new SSH key: ssh-keygen -t rsa -C "your_email@example.com"
(2) Add your key to the ssh-agent: ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_rsa (id_rsa is the name)
